OL,3,CConservative peer Zac Goldsmith banned
OL,4,Cfrom driving for 12 months after
OL,5,Cspeeding
OL,7,FFormer environment minister Zac
OL,8,FGoldsmith has been banned from driving
OL,9,Ffor a year after he was caught
OL,10,Fspeeding seven times last year.
OL,12,FThe Conservative peer, 49, broke speed
OL,13,Flimits in his hybrid electric
OL,14,FVolkswagen Golf on London roads in
OL,15,FPaddington, Chelsea and Twickenham
OL,16,Fbetween April and November 2023.
OL,18,FHe was also caught speeding on two
OL,19,Fmotorways, most recently in December,
OL,20,FWestminster Magistrates' Court heard.
