OL,3,CConservative peer Zac Goldsmith banned
OL,4,Cfrom driving for 12 months after
OL,5,Cspeeding
OL,7,FIn May, August and November of the
OL,8,Fsame year, he broke the 40mph limit on
OL,9,Fthe A316 in Twickenham by twice
OL,10,Fdriving at 46mph and once at 47mph.
OL,12,FHe was also caught driving at 62mph in
OL,13,Fa 50 zone at the M25 intersection with
OL,14,Fthe M3 in December, and at 73mph
OL,15,Fbetween junctions 20 and 19 of the M4
OL,16,Fin September ` breaking a 50mph
OL,17,Ftemporary speed limit.
OL,19,FLord Goldsmith had been banned from
OL,20,Fdriving since January, when an interim
OL,21,Fdisqualification was imposed.
